  "question_id": "4f69094e-2345-4d2d-9780-6e3c69d525de",
  "short_text": "Right Angled Triangle - 5",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print the **Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n  *\r\n **\r\n***\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as the **Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\r\n\r\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **4** rows as shown in the given image. \r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-right-angled-triangle-5.png' widthPercent='70'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates one space (\" \").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates a star (\"*\").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n   *\r\n  **\r\n ***\r\n****\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "4b4a1f8b-7148-4ed0-b038-0833e49649a6",
      "code_content": "rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, rows + 1):\n    \n    spaces = \" \" * (rows - each_number)\n    stars = \"*\" * (each_number)\n    print(spaces + stars)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
